enthalpy but opposite algebraic signs may occur, and in this case, the resulting DSC signal would
be zero. Thus, a heat ﬂow signal of zero during heating does not necessarily mean that no reactions
are taking place. In addition, the peak temperature of a certain heating DSC peak is not necessarily
equal to the intensity maximum of the related microstructural reaction [
